<faculty_text>Michael J. Sandel (Government)</faculty_text>
<description>What should be the role of money and markets in our society? Are there some things that money should not be able to buy? For example: Should people be permitted to buy sex, votes, babies, citizenship, or college admission? What about buying and selling the right to pollute, procreate, immigrate, discriminate, or to hunt endangered species? Should we use markets to allocate health care, education, and military service?</description>
